My Top 10 Questions to Prioritize

If management doesn’t have time for all 43 questions, these are the ones I’d prioritize:

1. What is the official business objective of the Reserve Recommendation Agent?
2. Why is the reserve formula Base Loss × (1 + Severity Buffer + Fraud Buffer) used?
3. Who defined the severity buffer percentages (30%, 20%, 10%, 5%)?
4. Why is the fraud buffer calculated as fraud_score / 1000?
5. Why is the fraud buffer capped at 15%?
6. Should the reserve calculation always use the latest loss assessment, or only approved assessments?
7. Should reserve recommendations ever be constrained by policy coverage limits?
8. Under what conditions should the reserve be recalculated after the initial recommendation?
9. Should business constants (severity buffers and fraud cap) be configurable rather than hardcoded?
10. What is the expected interaction between the AI-recommended reserve and the adjuster’s manually entered reserve, and which value should downstream agents use?

These questions focus on the areas where your current implementation contains implicit assumptions. Getting them answered will give you documented business requirements rather than requiring you to infer the intent from the code.
